quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  43,74,"Indeed, the criminals abide in the punishment of Hell"
  43,75,"which is never palliated for them, and in it they are devastated."
  43,76,"Yet in no way did We do them injustice, but it was they who were the unjust."
  43,77,"And they cried<a class=""sup""><sup>f </sup></a>, “O Malek{1}, let your Lord finish us off.” He said, “You are staying.",footnotes:1:Malek is the angel in charge of Hell.
  43,78,"We certainly came to you with the truth, but most of you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>are hateful of the truth.”"
  43,79,"Or have they contrived to do something? So indeed, We too are contriving."
  43,80,"Or do they think that We cannot hear their secret and their private conversations? Yes indeed, Our messengers are by them, writing down."
  43,81,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “If the All-Merciful had <span class=""h"">a child<sup foot_note=""81119"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, I would be the first of<i class=""s"">(his) </i>worshipers.”"
  43,82,"Highly Exalted is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, the Lord of the Throne, beyond what they describe."
  43,83,"So leave<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>them to blunder and play until they <span class=""h"">meet<sup foot_note=""81120"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>their day which they are promised."
  43,84,"And it is He who in the heaven is God, and in the earth is God, and He is the All-Wise, the All-Knowing."
  43,85,"And supremely blessed be the One to Whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them, and Who alone has knowledge of the Hour, and to Whom <span class=""h"">you</span><a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a><span class=""h"">are returned<sup foot_note=""81121"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>."
  43,86,"And those they call upon apart from Him are incapable of intercession, except those who testify to the truth knowingly."
  43,87,"And surely if you asked them, “Who created them?” they would certainly say, “Allah.” So how can they be averted<i class=""s"">(from the truth) </i>?"
  43,88,"And<i class=""s"">(God hears) </i>his{1}statement: “My Lord, indeed, these are people who do not believe.”",footnotes:1:That of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him).
  43,89,"Then grant<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>them amnesty and say, “Peace.” For <span class=""h"">they<sup foot_note=""81123"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">shall come to know</span>."
